The paper deals with sequence generation models, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model architecture and training techniques, which are related to machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The model's flexibility and ability to handle dynamic length changes suggest that it may also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's experiments involve tasks such as machine translation and text summarization, which are often studied in the computer vision (CV) and NLP fields, respectively, making cs.CV a possible sub-category as well.
